text: Year 105 (CV) was a common year starting on Wednesday (link will display the full calendar) of the Julian calendar. At the time, it was known as the Year of the Consulship of Candidus and Iulius (or, less commonly, year 858 Ab urbe condita). Writing 105 for this year has been used since the early medieval period, when the Anno Domini calendar era became the normal method in Europe for naming years. == Births == * Alexander of Abonoteichus, Greek mystic and oracle (d. 170) * Han Shangdi, Chinese emperor of the Han Dynasty (d. 106) * Marcus Sedatius Severianus, Roman politician (d. 161) == Deaths == * June 24 - Gnaeus Afranius Dexter, Roman politician * Gnaeus Pompeius Longinus, Roman politician * Marcus Valerius Probus, Roman grammarian * Pacorus II, king of the Parthian Empire * Plutarch, bishop of Byzantium
